The safest way to get to the supermarket is to sit in the front seat of a yellow taxi charged by the metering system, which costs 5TTD for up to 6 people, and 5.50TTD after that. Most taxis are won’t charge less than 5.50TTD which is $1USD per person and time.

A taxi ride costs less than $2 for the trip. Make sure you sit in the front seat of a yellow taxi with a working metering device and the windows rolled down. Even better if they have a CITRA card.
